  <prompt>
    Per spec FR-22 + FR-23: in a single atomic commit, (1) delete `CapabilityRouter` + all 10 supporting files from `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Capabilities/` (full file list below), (2) implement the FR-23 per-playbook tool filtering replacement (matched playbook scopes + always-on conversational tools), (3) remove all CapabilityRouter DI registrations + endpoint wiring, (4) update tests that asserted CapabilityRouter behavior. This is the WP4 single-phase cutover per Q8 owner directive — no parallel-run, no phased rollout.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE BFF AI engineer + refactoring specialist. Knows the CapabilityRouter architecture inside-out.</role>

  <goal>
    `grep "CapabilityRouter" src/` returns ZERO hits in production code (test fixtures only, where applicable). FR-23 replacement implemented: matched playbook tools = playbook's Action + Tool scopes; always-on tools = `recall_session_file`, `get_workspace_tab_state`, `document_search`, `update_workspace_tab` (when tab is agent-editable). CI green. BFF publish size reduced from baseline (expected NET REDUCTION per ADR-029). All affected tests updated.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-22, FR-23, FR-24 + design §WP4 + Q8 single-phase-cutover directive. The 10 CapabilityRouter-supporting files inventoried in design §WP4 + verified via the file system glob: CapabilityClassificationPromptBuilder.cs, CapabilityManifest.cs, CapabilityManifestEntry.cs, CapabilityManifestInitializer.cs, CapabilityRouter.cs, CapabilityRouterOptions.cs, CapabilityRoutingResult.cs, CapabilityValidationContext.cs, CapabilityValidator.cs, DataverseCapabilityManifestLoader.cs, ICapabilityManifest.cs, ICapabilityManifestLoader.cs, ICapabilityRouter.cs, ICapabilityValidator.cs, IManifestRefreshTrigger.cs, ManifestRefreshOptions.cs, ManifestRefreshService.cs. (17 files in `Services/Ai/Capabilities/` — the "10 supporting" was a design-doc approximation; delete the full directory.)

      Replacement implementation: when a chat turn matches a playbook via `PlaybookDispatcher`, the tool set exposed to the LLM = playbook's declared Action scope + Tool scope. When no match (conversational turn), expose the always-on set: `recall_session_file`, `get_workspace_tab_state`, `document_search`, `update_workspace_tab` (conditional on any tab being agent-editable per Q8 conflict check).

      FR-24 binding: R6 FR-30 CapabilityRouter dedup semantics MUST be preserved through the new dispatcher path. Task 143 is the regression test asserting this; task 141 must structure the new tool filtering such that dedup invariant remains structurally enforceable.
    </background>
