  <steps>
    <step order="1">Take a Phase 6 final BFF publish-size measurement as the pre-deletion baseline: `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`. Record at `notes/handoffs/141-pre-deletion-publish.md`.</step>
    <step order="2">Inventory call sites: `grep -rn "CapabilityRouter\|ICapabilityRouter\|ICapabilityValidator\|ICapabilityManifest\|ManifestRefresh\|DataverseCapability" src/` and `tests/`. Catalog every file referencing any deleted type.</step>
    <step order="3">For each call site, decide: (a) call site removed entirely (most common — the caller was Layer 0.5 routing), (b) call site rewired to `PlaybookDispatcher` + new tool-filtering logic. Document the decision per call site in working notes.</step>
    <step order="4">Implement FR-23 replacement logic in `SprkChatAgentFactory` (or appropriate prompt-assembly site): when a turn maps to a playbook via `PlaybookDispatcher`, derive the tool list from the playbook's Action + Tool scopes. When no playbook match (conversational), use the always-on set: `recall_session_file`, `get_workspace_tab_state`, `document_search`, `update_workspace_tab` (conditional on any tab being agent-editable).</step>
    <step order="5">Wire FR-24: ensure the new tool filtering preserves dedup semantics (one user intent → one playbook → one destination → no duplicate tool exposure). The dedup test in task 143 will verify this.</step>
    <step order="6">Remove ALL DI registrations for `ICapabilityRouter`, `ICapabilityValidator`, `ICapabilityManifest`, `ICapabilityManifestLoader`, `IManifestRefreshTrigger`, `ManifestRefreshService` from `AiModule.cs` (or wherever registered).</step>
    <step order="7">Delete the 17 files under `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Capabilities/` (per Glob inventory). Verify `Services/Ai/Capabilities/` directory empty (or removed).</step>
    <step order="8">Delete or migrate tests in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Capabilities/`. Replace with new tool-filtering unit tests asserting FR-23 behavior.</step>
    <step order="9">Run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` — must succeed without warnings about missing types.</step>
    <step order="10">Run `dotnet test` — full suite must pass. Failures here likely indicate missed call sites; iterate steps 2-4 as needed.</step>
    <step order="11">Measure post-deletion BFF publish size: `dotnet publish -c Release ...`. Compute delta vs step 1 baseline. EXPECT NET REDUCTION (binding per FR-22 hypothesis); report at `notes/handoffs/141-post-deletion-publish.md`.</step>
    <step order="12">Run code-review + adr-check (Step 9.5 FULL gates).</step>
    <step order="13">Single atomic commit — ALL deletions + replacement code + test updates in ONE commit with clear message referencing FR-22 + FR-23.</step>
    <step order="14">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 141 → ✅. Pre/post publish-size handoffs link from the index entry.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Grep">Inventory CapabilityRouter call sites across src/ + tests/</tool>
    <tool name="Read">All 17 Capabilities/*.cs files + their consumers</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Apply replacement logic in SprkChatAgentFactory + remove DI registrations</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">Delete files; dotnet build/test/publish</tool>
    <tool name="Write">Pre/post publish-size handoffs</tool>
  </tools>

